					ovary ovoid, 2-2.5 mm long;
					stigma subsessile, ± flat, (1- or) 2-4-lobed and each lobe again few- to many- (up to 15-)lobulate or serrate.

Fruits 1 or 2 per infructescence, ellipsoid or broadly obovoid, sometimes ridged, 1.8-2.2 by 1.2-1.8 cm, with mealy hairs 0.1-0.3 mm long;
					dry pericarp l(-2) mm thick;
					fruiting pedicel (3-) 4-11 mm long.

Leaves membranous or thinly coriaceous, at first with indumentum mainly of stellate golden brown or grey hairs 0.1 mm long, early or late glabrescent, oblong to lanceolate, parallel-sided or broadest at or below the middle, 6-18(-24) by 1.5-4(-7) cm, apex acute or acuminate, base attenuate, rarely rounded;
