					ovary fusiform or flask-shaped, 6 by 2-2.5 mm, gynophore 1 mm, all densely minutely grey-brown pubescent.

Fruits solitary, ± ellipsoid-fusiform, 6.5-7.5 by 3.5-4.5 cm, apex narrowed, base somewhat contracted into a pseudostalk, 3-8 mm long, early glabrescent, brown, usually set with conspicuous coarse pale pustules or lenticels;
